### 0) Health
GET http://localhost:8000/healthz


### 1) Open SSE stream (creates the session)
# Required header for SSE:
GET http://localhost:8000/mcp
Accept: text/event-stream

# After this request runs, look at the response headers:
# - Copy the value of the `Mcp-Session-Id` header from the response.
#   The VS Code REST Client shows headers above the body. Save it for the next steps.


### 2) Initialize (MUST be the first JSON-RPC request on the session)
# Replace <SESSION_ID> with the value from step 1.
POST http://localhost:8000/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: <SESSION_ID>

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "initialize",
  "params": {
    "protocolVersion": "2025-03-26",
    "capabilities": {
      "roots": { "listChanged": true },
      "sampling": {}
    },
    "clientInfo": { "name": "VSCode REST Client", "version": "dev" }
  }
}


### 3) Tell the server weâ€™re ready (initialized notification)
POST http://localhost:8000/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: <SESSION_ID>

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "notifications/initialized"
}


### 4) Call your tool (now allowed)
POST http://localhost:8000/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: <SESSION_ID>

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 2,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "greet",
    "arguments": { "name": "Chris" }
  }
}


### 5) Close the session (optional)
DELETE http://localhost:8000/mcp
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: <SESSION_ID>
